MIS = Management Information System

It is a system that collects, processes, stores, and presents business data to help managers make decisions.

Simple Definition

MIS helps convert raw data into useful information for business decision-making.

Example

A company has daily sales data:

| Day       | Sales   |
| --------- | ------- |
| Monday    | ₹10,000 |
| Tuesday   | ₹12,000 |
| Wednesday | ₹15,000 |

======

aw Data:

10000
12000
15000

Using MIS functions:

=SUM(B2:B4)

Result:

₹37,000 Total Sales

Now management can understand business performance quickly.

